<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Using Tempo as a Weapon</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Fast play when ahead:</span> Playing quickly when you're leading creates psychological pressure. Your opponent feels rushed, makes hasty decisions, and burns extra time double-checking. Your speed signals confidence.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Deliberate pace when behind:</span> When trailing, take your full time to find optimal plays. Rushed decisions when behind compound the deficit. A slow, methodical approach also denies your opponent the satisfaction of momentum.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Common Time Traps</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">The phantom bingo:</span> Spending 4 minutes rearranging tiles for a bingo that doesn't exist. If you haven't found it in 90 seconds, it probably isn't there — play your second-best option.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Over-optimising:</span> Comparing a 28-point play against a 31-point play for 2 minutes. The 3-point difference doesn't justify 2 minutes of clock. Play the first good option you find.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Challenge deliberation:</span> Wasting 60+ seconds deciding whether to challenge. Set a rule: if you're less than 70% sure it's invalid, don't challenge. Decide in under 10 seconds.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Score verification spirals:</span> Recounting your opponent's last play multiple times. Trust the math once — verify during their next turn if concerned, not on your own clock.</p>
  </div>
</div>

